Yes, there is a minimum level. As the article says the foci work from level 34 onwards.
If you get a message like "Solusek Ro does not believe in doing things half" this does not say your faction is bad or that you should be a follower of Sol Ro. It tells you that you have not yet handed in ALL the 4 CORRECT items to receive a focus item.
The items listed in the article are correct, the most probable reason why Kazzyr failed has been pointed out by Cyriel, make sure you have the correct shovel.<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>I did all 4 of these, and I accidentally criss crossed the items for the broom and the shovel. But then I turend in the rest of the tiems, and then completed the items for BOTH items and the NPC handed be both focus items.  This was back before they gave stuff back to you also.  But the NPC will hold the items for each focus and will hand it out as soon as the 4th item is handed in.  <br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>Dark-Boned Skeleton's in Najena have a chance of dropping any 4 of the focus quest items.

